<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="L" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Lean2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Lean,</orth> adj. 1) wanting flesh, meager, thin: <bibl n="shak. ven 136" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 136</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ven 136" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 136</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.7.158" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 7, 158</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.341" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 341</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.341" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 341</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tn 4.2.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. IV, 2, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.2.201" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 2, 201</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.358" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 358</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.358" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 358</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.2.294" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 2, 294</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.2.35" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 2, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.2.11" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.104" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 3, 104</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.2.194" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 2, 194</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 2.2.113" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 113</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 4.3.25" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 3, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.11.37" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 11, 37</bibl>. <cit><quote>lank and l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 708" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 708</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the clergy's bags are lank and l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.3.132" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 3, 132</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) not rich, barren, sterile: <cit><quote>lards the l. earth,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.2.116" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 2, 116</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.3.129" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 3, 129</bibl>.
<lb />3) bare, stripped: <cit><quote>l., rent and beggared by the strumpet wind,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 2.6.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 6, 19</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the trees, though summer, yet forlorn and l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.94" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 94</bibl></cit>.
<lb />4) barren of thought: <cit><quote>l. penury within that pen doth dwell,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 84.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 84, 5</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>fat paunches have l. pates,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.26" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 26</bibl></cit>.
<lb />5) poor, insignificant: <cit><quote>I have but l. luck in the match,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 3.2.93" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 2, 93</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>out of my l. and low ability,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.378" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 4, 378</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>whereof the hangman hath no l. wardrobe,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.2.82" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 2, 82</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>let not a --er action rend us,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 2.2.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 2, 19</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>